Description: Limestone ostracon: on one side only, a sketch design in black ink of the names of Ramses VI, the title of the throne-name being clumsily written.
Curator's comments: See also O. Leipzig 1656 (E. Brunner-Traut, 'Die altägyptischen Scherbenbilder’ (Wiesbaden, 1956), p. 129, no. 166).
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (389832) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/389832)
